{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGVector","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CGVector"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, the center point of an annotation view is placed at the geographic"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"coordinate point of the associated annotation. If you do not want the view to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be centered, you can use this property to reposition the view. The offset’s"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dx"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"dy","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" values are measured in points. Positive offset values move the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"annotation view down and to the right, while negative values move it up and to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the left."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Set the offset if the annotation view’s visual center point is somewhere other","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"than the logical center of the view. For example, the view may contain an image"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that depicts a downward-pointing pushpin or thumbtack, with the tip positioned"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at the center-bottom of the view. In that case, you would set the offset’s "},{"code":"dx","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to zero and its "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dy"},{"text":" to half the height of the view.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"]]},"metadata":{"externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNAnnotationView(py)centerOffset","remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-native\/blob\/main\/platform\/ios\/src\/MLNAnnotationView.h#L159","fileName":"MLNAnnotationView.h"},"symbolKind":"property","roleHeading":"Instance Property","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"}],"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"title":"centerOffset","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"}]},"sections":[],"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView/centerOffset":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset","title":"centerOffset","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view."}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"role":"collection","abstract":[{"text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","title":"MapLibre","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"objects to handle the display."}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotation"}],"title":"MLNAnnotation"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView":{"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"},{"type":"text","text":" class is responsible for marking a point annotation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with a view. Annotation views represent an annotation object, which is an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"object that corresponds to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","isActive":true},{"text":" protocol. When an annotation’s","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"geographic coordinate is visible in the map view, the map view asks its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"delegate to a corresponding annotation view. If an annotation view is created","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"with a reuse identifier, the map view may recycle the view when it goes","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"offscreen."}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","role":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview","fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotationView","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"MLNAnnotationView"}}}